metadata.name: Noir et Blanc #187
metadata.description:
Timeless Generative Art in Black & White.

With 8 subtle levels of finesse, a grid ranging from 1 to 21, and an extensive range of offsets, the possibilities to create modern geometric designs are simply endless in this series.

Perfect for prints, each artwork can be collected according to its finesse and grid, allowing the possibility of creating amazing diptychs and triptychs. 

Made with P5.js and a strong love for Black & White artwork.

metadata.name: Acequia #155
metadata.description:
Acequia (‚Äúah-seh-kee-uh‚Äù) - a Spanish adaptation of the Arabic word as-sƒÅqiya, meaning ‚Äúwater carrier‚Äù. 

In our second collaboration, Rich and Rick are back with our blend of generative code, intricate design, attention to detail, and a splash of charm. 

‚Ä®Acequias are traditional irrigation canals used to distribute rainwater and snowmelt along a complex network of narrow channels. They are found in Spain, the American Southwest, and northern Mexico, where they are essential for sustaining fields, orchards, and gardens in semi-arid regions. ‚Ä®‚Ä®
Our aim in this series is to capture the essence of these waterways in bold geometric designs. Each piece is inspired by a mountain village or town in Andalusia (southern Spain). 

The location determines the cube designs and construction rules that are used to build the final output. These are combined with striking day/night palettes, outline styles, scales, climates, and a few surprises of course!


Controls (in live view): 

- Press [p] to pause water animation 
- Press [e] to complete water animation 
- Press [r] to reset water animation 
- Press [s] to save the current image 
- Press [h] for a high-res output suitable for printing 
- Press [b] to toggle the border

metadata.name: Sa·πÖkhƒÅra #63
metadata.description:
üéß CLICK/TAP FOR SOUND ON

Sa·πÖkhƒÅra is a portrait of symbolic consciousness in three movements.

Colorful automata represents direct experience: touch, sight, hearing, smell, taste and thought in a ceaseless flow of novelty.

The automata congeals into form alluding to the way our minds close over experience with symbolic representation, like a plastic bag coming down over a kaleidoscope of butterflies. What was free in the open air is now trapped. What was previously wild and unpredictable is now under control, frozen and communicable.

The form‚Äôs dispersal mimics the release of mental formation, the unbinding of a symbol, the letting go of a belief. It‚Äôs a visceral reflection of the process of ceasing to identify with separateness. To strain the previous metaphor, it‚Äôs the opening of the bag and letting the butterflies return to the flow of raw, boundless experience.

‚Äî

K.C. Austin
From his cockpit in the Blue Ridge Mountains K.C. Austin (aka bzor) spends his days shaping realtime software art systems of all stripes. Informed by game design, modular synths, virtual reality and consciousness research, K.C. plays shaders like a fiddle and fashions creative pipelines like a spider spins webs.

James Paterson
Fascinated by the relationship between ancient and futuristic mediums, James Paterson has been exploring a unique synthesis of drawing, code, animation and sculpture under the moniker ‚ÄòPresstube‚Äô since 1999. Paterson draws inspiration from meditation, molecular biology, music, parenting and psychedelics - the seen, the heard, the felt, the cognized.

metadata.name: Broken Symmetries #1/3 #58
metadata.description:
"It was the best of times, it was the worst of times, it was the age of wisdom, it was the age of foolishness, it was the epoch of belief, it was the epoch of incredulity, it was the season of Light, it was the season of Darkness, it was the spring of hope, it was the winter of despair, we had everything before us, we had nothing before us..."
                                      Charles Dickens

This piece is the first in a planed series of three intended as studies on composition.

It is built entirely on thi.ng/umbrella libraries and template:

https://github.com/thi-ng/fxhash-tpl

Keyboard shortcuts

- 1 : render @ original resolution
- 2 : render @ 2 x resolution
- 4 : render @ 4 x resolution
- x : download canvas as PNG @ current resolution
- s : download canvas as SVG @ current resolution; This can be used with a plotter.

metadata.name: Departure Within Shattered Windmills #43
metadata.description:
I wrote the following when reviewing the outputs...

The wind is gone,
My windmill falls,
I reach out to catch the pieces.
Half fall in my right hand,
The others in my left,
Two stacks of colored paper.
I‚Äôm holding my windmill,
I feel the breeze in my hair.
Each hand is empty,
My windmill rises,
I can see the wind.

'Departure Within Shattered Windmills' was originally inspired by suprematism, and then started to gain more complexity. It is still a combination of simple features, subdivided quads drawn on different planes of perspective. Chaos simulated by many organized grids. Countless pieces of a windmill.

25% of the royalties for each edition will pass to the original minter.

Each output is generated from code written in p5js.

Created by Eric Davidson. 2022.

metadata.name: Bayerlinge #27
metadata.description:
"Bayerlinge" is motivated by the artworks of Herbert Bayer (1900-1985). The Upper Austrian born artist spent his life in Germany and the United Stated and also worked as graphic designer, painter, and many more.

I was inspired by his piece "Foursome" from 1971 and aimed to deliver the same feeling in a generative setting. The token expands upon Bayer's arrangement, adding different shapes and for more than the overlapping 2x2 setup.

The key press "s" or "S" lets you save a high resolution image.

metadata.name: Infinite Scaling System #122
metadata.description:
This generative system has a beginning, but no ending. It scales infinitely in different directions as unlimited shapes are added. Special care was taken to avoid memory overflows, impossibly big numbers, and poor performance. 

Rendered using P5.JS

metadata.name: LGBTQ+ Lives Matter #4
metadata.description:
Throughout history, we have witnessed many movements and revolutions, but none of them could bring long-term success to the people.
This time, it's time to remove the biggest and most CONTRASTED border in human history (i.e. gender binary).
Removing this border can completely change the rules of the game; Laws, cultures, economics and anything else you can think of will also improve.
In this collection, you see the shifting of boundaries and people, and the reason for creating this work is that the viewer can easily re-imagine sexual boundaries and sexual tendencies.

Did you know that October is LGBTQ+ history month? It‚Äôs a 31-day celebration to honor lesbian, gay, bisexual, transgender, and queer achievement and influence on the world and a time to learn more about the history of LGBTQ+ rights.

Since our creation, Black Lives Matter has been about LGBTQ+ lives ‚Äî because all Black lives matter, period. It‚Äôs a priority for us to always put LGBTQ+ voices at the center of the conversation, and it‚Äôs important that we highlight the intersectionalities of being Black and LGBTQ+ in our movement.
